The paper deals with the Graver basis of integer programming, which is a topic in discrete mathematics and theoretical computer science. The paper also involves algorithms and complexity analysis, which are common in the sub-categories of cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.CC (Computational Complexity), and cs.LG (Machine Learning). The use of matrices and linear algebra suggests that the paper may also be relevant to cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) and cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory).
